10:07 AM Defendant Dashawn D Buford appeared by video, in custody, Attorney Nathan J. Heim for Dashawn D Buford appeared by video, Attorney Marconi De Franca Barros for State of Wisconsin appeared by video. 
Count 1, Battery-DVO, repeater, No contest plea entered. 
Count 3, Disorderly Conduct-DVO, repeater, No contest plea entered.
Rights explained. Convicted. 
Count 1: 
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of two (2) years. That is one (1) year initial confinement followed by one (1) year of extended supervision. Execution of the sentence is stayed and the defendant placed on probation DOC for three (3) years.
Count 3: 
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of two (2) years. That is one (1) year initial confinement followed by one (1) year of extended supervision. Execution of the sentence is stayed and the defendant placed on probation DOC for three (3) years. 
Conditions of probation: 
1)	Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process including but not limited to anger management and domestic abuse counseling;
2)	Seek and maintain fulltime occupation of some kind with the agent's approval;
3)	Pay court costs
4)	Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
5)	No contact with the victim unless permitted by the agent; 
6)	Maintain absolute sobriety;
7)	Submit to random drug and/or alcohol screens and pay for the same;
8)	Submit to DNA sample
The court finds that the defendant has 22 days credit on count 1 if revoked. 
Minutes.
